National chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Iyorchia Ayu has stated that the party is working hard to win the presidential election in 2023. Ayu spoke on Wednesday night during a meeting of the board of trustees (BoT) and national executive committee (NEC) members at the party’s headquarters in Abuja. The PDP chairman said members are working “around the clock” to reposition the party and hold a successful presidential primary. Also Read: Support Me To Bring Back Good Old Days, Anyim Tells Kaduna PDP Delegates “We have worked round the clock on the details in preparation for the special convention,” he said. “We are not only getting more united, but we are also getting more determined to work hard and reclaim power. “Everybody is working hard. I believe with this spirit we will definitely do very well in the forthcoming election and nothing will stop us from taking over power come May next year.”